<comment type="function">
<text evidence="1">Antitoxin component of a toxin-antitoxin (TA) module. Neutralizes the toxic effect of cognate toxin HipA. Binds to operator sites with the consensus sequence 5-'TATCCN(8)GGATA-3' to repress the hipBA operon promoter; binding to DNA induces a 70 degree bend.</text>
</comment>
<comment type="enzyme regulation">
<text evidence="2">Degraded by Lon protease; degradation is inhibited in a HipA-HipB complex and when bound to the operator consensus sequence dsDNA.</text>
</comment>
<comment type="subunit">
<text evidence="1 3">Homodimer. Forms a HipA(2)HipB(2) heterotetramer which can interact with DNA. This complex also blocks the toxic activity of HipA.</text>
</comment>
<comment type="PTM">
<text>Degraded by Lon protease in vivo; half-life is 17 minutes in wild-type cells and over 200 minutes in a lon deletion strain. In vitro degradation by Lon is Mg(2+)-ATP-dependent.</text>
</comment>
<comment type="disruption phenotype">
<text evidence="1">Cannot be disrupted, suggesting it is a functional antitoxin. No visible phenotype when the hipBA operon is deleted.</text>
</comment>
<comment type="similarity">
<text>Contains 1 HTH cro/C1-type DNA-binding domain.</text>
</comment>
